    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5752/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1925</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received June 22.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 595</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that, in compliance
                    with the Department’s Instruction No. 221, of April 21, 1925,<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d166fn1">See footnote 41, <ref target="#pg_227">p. 227</ref>.</note>
                    I addressed to the Madrid Foreign Office a Note, No. 316, dated May 8, 1925,
                    from the enclosed copy of which<note n="53" xml:id="d166fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    it will be seen that I informed the Acting Foreign Minister of the appointment
                    of a Customs Attaché and three Assistants to this Embassy, and requested
                    recognition of them in their respective capacities by the Spanish
                    Government.</p>
                <p>A copy and translation of the Note of reply of the Foreign Office are transmitted
                        herewith.<note n="53" xml:id="d166fn3">Not printed.</note> In it I am
                    advised that the Spanish Government, while not according to the officials in
                    reference the status of attachés to this Embassy, is willing to grant to them,
                    upon request, such customs facilities as are usually extended to members <pb
                        facs="0361" n="235" xml:id="pg_235"/> of diplomatic missions, if in the
                    discharge of their duties they are required to visit Spain.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alexander P. Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
